Version bump to fix RST rendering on PyPI.

The RST library in PyPI is very strict now - and displays files which don't conform as plain-text.
The one on github is much more lax, so I hadn't noticed the missing blank line...
Oops.

Fix for next part of #48 - index access before attr

Added note to the README explaining the main problem - x.y should try x.y first, and then x['y'] *IF DESIRED*.  It was the wrong way round, and always on.  Now it's better.
